result.execSummary:
The defendant Autumn Elaine Durham was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Endanger Safety/Reckless Use of Firearm, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.20(2)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
*Court does not order restitution amount at this time. Court orders: victim to submit proof of expenses as to windshield and seat repair within 45 days.  Court is inclined to make restitution order as to that amount.  Court makes no determination as to fault in traffic accident.
*Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.
*Court ordered defendant to pay all applicable court costs and surcharges.
*As to all costs and surcharges, Court orders amounts to be deducted from bail on deposit.  Remaining balance to be returned to the person who posted. If revoked, DOC shall collect up to 25% of prison funds.  Remaining balance to be paid during the period of extended supervision.  Any unpaid portion to convert to a civil judgment.

*Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon she may never possess a firearm or body armor.  Court advised defendant that her voting rights are suspended and she may not vote in any election until she civil rights are restored.

*No contact with victim MILTON J.;
*No new offenses.

*Continue with mental health treatment and follow recommendations.
*Complete anger management programming.
